---

# 8. Time Complexity Summary

| Operation | Time |
| --------- | ---- |
| Push      | O(1) |
| Pop       | O(1) |
| Peek      | O(1) |
| isEmpty   | O(1) |
| Size      | O(1) |
| Search    | O(n) |

---

# 9. Stack vs Queue

| Stack           | Queue             |
| --------------- | ----------------- |
| LIFO            | FIFO              |
| Insert at Top   | Insert at Rear    |
| Remove from Top | Remove from Front |
| One End         | Two Ends          |
| Plate Stack     | Ticket Queue      |

Example

Stack

```
Push:
10
20
30

Pop Order:

30
20
10
```

Queue

```
Enqueue:
10
20
30

Dequeue Order:

10
20
30
```

---

# 10. Applications of Stack

Stacks are used in many real-world scenarios:

* Function Calls (Call Stack)
* Undo/Redo in editors
* Browser Back Button
* Expression Evaluation
* Parentheses Matching
* Backtracking Algorithms
* DFS (Depth First Search)
* Recursion

---

# 11. Common Interview Questions

* Valid Parentheses
* Min Stack
* Next Greater Element
* Daily Temperatures
* Largest Rectangle in Histogram
* Stock Span Problem
* Evaluate Reverse Polish Notation
* Decode String
* Remove K Digits
* Asteroid Collision

---

# 12. Common Mistakes Beginners Make

### ❌ Pop from Empty Stack

```java
stack.pop();
```

Throws

```
EmptyStackException
```

Always check

```java
if(!stack.isEmpty()){
    stack.pop();
}
```

---

### ❌ Peek from Empty Stack

```java
stack.peek();
```

Also throws

```
EmptyStackException
```

---

### ❌ Thinking Bottom is the Top

Remember

```
Top
 ↓
30
20
10
```

Only **30** can be removed.

---

# 13. One Analogy to Remember Everything

Imagine a **stack of books** on a table.

```
Top
 ↓
Math
Science
English
```

You place a new book **only on the top**.

```
History

Math
Science
English
```

If you want the **English** book, you **must first remove History, then Math, then Science**.

That is **LIFO (Last In, First Out)**.

---

# 14. Cheat Sheet (Revision in 30 Seconds)

* **Stack = LIFO (Last In, First Out)**
* **Push = Add at Top**
* **Pop = Remove Top**
* **Peek = View Top**
* **isEmpty() = Check if Empty**
* **size() = Number of Elements**
* **Push, Pop, Peek = O(1)**
* **Used in Recursion, Browser History, Undo/Redo, DFS, Expression Evaluation**
* **Remember the Plate Stack Analogy** 🍽️

This format matches your Linked List notes and is ideal for quick revision before interviews or solving LeetCode stack problems.
